snippet: The prime minister announced that the chief minister in Baluchistan Province, Mohammed Aslam Raisani, had been dismissed and the Parliament there had been dissolved.
abstract: Pakistani Prime Min Raja Pervez Ashraf announces that Mohammed Aslam Raisani, chief minister of Baluchistan Province, has been dismissed, provincial Parliament has been dissolved and control of province is being handed to its governor; announcement is concession to members of Hazara minority, who have protested in street for days after suicide bombers killed almost 100 people in Quetta.
lead_paragraph: The prime minister announced that the chief minister in Baluchistan Province, Mohammed Aslam Raisani, had been dismissed and the Parliament there had been dissolved.

headline.seo: An Ouster in Concession to Pakistan Protesters
headline.main: Concession After Days of Protest in Pakistan
headline.print_headline: Concession After Days Of Protest In Pakistan
